review_blob: Bottle - Looks fantastic. The texture reminds me of engine oil. Nice brown head. Great aroma, almost attacking my nose. Smells very roasted notes, coffee, dark chocolate, almonds. I can also smell notes of vanilla, cream and some sweet liquorice. Tastes even better. Heres roasted notes, coffee/espresso, dark chocolate, cocoa and vanilla. Starts sweet but quickly turns to a bitter hopy taste. Awesome beer. Feels like a fist punching your mouth after you swallowed it!

Bottle - Colour is amber and shimmers in red. Porous, fluffy light Beige head. On the nose theres some citrus notes, malt, sweet hops, some kind of wood and some metall. Starts with a sweetness but quickly turns into a hopy bitterness, with some vanilla, pepper, and citrus.

My first review here. Im new in the beer world but Ill give it a try! 
The colour is very dark brown, almost black with a light brown head that disappear pretty fast. On the nose theres a fruity sweetness, milk chocolate, candy, roasted bread, notes of liquorice and coffee. In my mouth I can taste chocolate, coffee, vanilla, and some dark bread. Not so creamy and theres not so long taste that I had expected but overall a great beer. Ill probably buy this beer again.
